WHAT DOES THE THROW KEYWORD DO?
	The throw keyword explicitly throws an exception back to the calling method.

WHAT DOES THE THROWS KEYWORD DO?
	This lets the compiler know that this method might throw a particular exception, and any calling method
	should deal with this by either throwing the exception further up the call stack, or catching it.

WHAT IS THE STRUCTURE OF A TRY/CATCH BLOCK?
	The try block is where your "risky" statement should be.
	The catch block handles exception by declaring it within its parameter, and dealing it with it in the body.

WHAT IS A RuntimeException?
	RuntimeException is the superclass of those exceptions that can be thrown
	during the normal operation of the JVM. A method isn't required to declare
	any subclasses of RuntimeException that might be thrown.